Catherine George is a popular British author of over 65 romance novels . Mills & Boon have published her novels since 1982 . Catherine George was born in a village on the Welsh - English border in Great Britain . When Catherine was only 18 years old she met a future engineer , and after marrying they went to live to Brazil , where they lived nine years . They returned to Great Britain to educate their son . There , they had a daughter , and Catherine had to raise her two children while her husband worked in Portugal , West Africa , and various countries of the Middle East . Now , their children are adults and have moved away . Catherine and her husband live in a house built at the end of Victoria 's reign in four acres of garden on the cliffs between the beautiful Wye Valley and the River Severn . 